# Docs theme base-aware links

GitHub Pages serves this site under `/joc/`. Plain `<a href="/packages/...">` in custom theme Vue **does not** get VitePress base rewriting and breaks after deploy.

## Required

- Import `docsHref` from `../docs-href` (or `./docs-href`) and wrap every internal path:
  - `:href="docsHref('/packages/browser-lifecycle/overview')"`
  - `:href="docsHref(pkg.docsLink)"`
- Or use `<DocsLink href="/packages/...">` / `<DocsLink :href="pkg.docsLink">`.
- External URLs (`https://...`) may stay bare or pass through `docsHref` (it leaves them unchanged).

## Do not

- Write `href="/getting-started/..."` or `:href="pkg.docsLink"` without `docsHref` / `DocsLink`.
- Hardcode `/joc/` in theme links — `withBase` / `docsHref` handle local (`/`) and Pages (`/joc/`).

## Check

`tests/docs-theme-links.test.ts` fails CI if bare absolute hrefs appear in theme Vue files.
